1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:02,000
Your Mac went to sleep.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,050
The download didn’t finish.

3
00:00:04,050 --> 00:00:09,237
Meet Wake My Mac: the native utility that keeps your Mac working when you step away.

4
00:00:09,237 --> 00:00:16,775
It watches the work that matters: agents, builds, renders, backups, downloads, and SSH.

5
00:00:16,775 --> 00:00:18,312
Set the rule once.

6
00:00:18,312 --> 00:00:19,950
Let the display sleep.

7
00:00:19,950 --> 00:00:21,337
Respect the battery.

8
00:00:21,337 --> 00:00:25,375
When the work is done, Wake My Mac lets your Mac sleep again.

9
00:00:25,375 --> 00:00:27,725
Not a permanent keep-awake switch.

10
00:00:27,725 --> 00:00:30,787
A smarter handoff between work and sleep.

11
00:00:30,787 --> 00:00:32,087
Wake My Mac.

12
00:00:32,087 --> 00:00:33,862
Keep going, on your terms.

